<h1>Arbaro - tree generation for povray</h1>

<p>
Arbaro is an implementation of the tree generating algorithm described
in <a href="http://www.cs.duke.edu/courses/cps124/spring08/assign/07_papers/p119-weber.pdf">
Jason Weber & Joseph Penn: "Creation and Rendering of Realistic Trees"</a>.
</p>
<p>
It's written in Java, so you can use it with any OS, wich is supported
by Java. You can download the Arbaro software from the 
<a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/arbaro/">project site</a> at
SourceForge.
<p>
It reads in an XML file with the tree parameters and writes out
Povray, DXF or Wavefront OBJ files. 

